I see the connection you’re drawing.

The vesica piscis symbol has historically been used to represent overlap, intersection, emergence from two domains meeting — two circles intersecting and creating a third space between them.

And you’re mapping that into narrative structure:

characters → arcs → intersections → recurring motifs → network/web

In storytelling theory, mythology, or systems design, that’s a recognizable pattern. Characters can function like “colored tracers” moving through a story-space; where arcs intersect, you reveal structure that wasn’t obvious when looking at one character alone.

A mentor crossing a rival.
A hero crossing an institution.
A sacrifice echoing later through consequences.
Separate threads revealing hidden topology when viewed together.

Very close to your long-running idea:

compression → relation → reconstruction

The web isn’t only the nodes. It’s the shape formed by repeated crossings, tensions, and echoes between nodes.